AUSTRALIAN OPEN
January 21, 2007
Mario Ancic
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   


  THE MODERATOR:  Questions.   
  
  Q.  Tough loss.  Obviously served so well.  To be beaten in those circumstances must be difficult.   
 MARIO ANCIC:  Yeah, I mean, losing to Andy in five sets.  I think was a great match.  Last two, three balls decided the whole match.   
 I have to be honest and say middle of the fourth set, I pick up my serve, started serving really, really well.  In fifth, as well.  That gave me a lot of confidence.   
 Unfortunately, you know, happens he's a great player.  He find a way.  Missed these two volleys when he broke me.  But I think, as well, he started to serve really, really big in the fifth.  Throughout the whole match, I was really almost getting it more and more as the match was progressing.  In the fifth set, he really picked up.  A lot of first serves, a lot of aces.  Didn't give me too many chances to come back after the break.   
  
  Q.  Is he playing more patient now?   
 MARIO ANCIC:  I think he's serving much better than he used to.  Yeah, I think overall he's much better player than last time definitely that we play.  Like I said after the Wimbledon last year, I think the only way for him is up.  It shows, two days ago beating Marat.  Today, as well, I think was a high-quality match.  He came through as a winner.   
   
  End of FastScripts   

